'''Jimi''' (Djimi), also known as '''Jimjimən''' and'' 'Um Falin'', is a [[Chadic language]] spoken in [[Cameroon]] in [[Far North Province]] on the Nigerian border in and around Bourrha.  Dialects are Djimi, Jimo, Malabu, Wadi, and Zumo.

